        "start": 58.503,
        "end": 97.445
      },
      {
        "segment": "The sub-Logoi had freedom to experience and experiment with consciousness, the experiences of the body, and the illumination of the spirit.",
        "start_offset": 441,
        "end_offset": 580,
        "start": 100.265,
        "end": 139.727
      },
      {
        "segment": "That having been said, we shall speak to the point of your query.",
        "start_offset": 581,
        "end_offset": 646,
        "start": 144.247,
        "end": 159.467
      },
      {
        "segment": "The first Logos to instill what you now see as free will, in the full sense, in its sub-Logoi came to this creation due to contemplation in depth of the concepts or possibilities of conceptualizations of what we have called the significators.",
        "start_offset": 647,
        "end_offset": 889,
        "start": 164.528,
        "end": 227.851
      },
      {
        "segment": "The Logos posited the possibility of the mind, the body, and the spirit as being complex.",
        "start_offset": 890,
        "end_offset": 979,
        "start": 227.871,
        "end": 244.591
      },
      {
        "segment": "In order for the significator to be what it is not, it then must be granted the free will of the Creator.",
        "start_offset": 980,
        "end_offset": 1085,
        "start": 247.332,
        "end": 275.573
      },
      {
        "segment": "This set in motion a quite lengthy, in your terms, series of Logoi improving or distilling this seed thought.",
